<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="141" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="141">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="141">
There has been disagreement among authors as to whether 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rohdendorf" authorityYear="1937" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Parasarcophaga" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Parasarcophaga parkeri" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parkeri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">Parasarcophaga parkeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a valid species or a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName family="Sarcophagidae" genus="S." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="S. aegyptica" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" rank="species" species="aegyptica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">S. aegyptica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Rohdendorf, BB" journalOrPublisher="Izdatelstvo Akademii Nauk SSSR, Moskva-Leningrad" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" refId="B30" refString="Rohdendorf, BB, 1937. Fam. Sarcophagidae (part 1), Fauna SSSR, New Series, No. 12. Izdatelstvo Akademii Nauk SSSR, Moskva-Leningrad" title="Fam. Sarcophagidae (part 1), Fauna SSSR, New Series, No. 12." year="1937">Rohdendorf (1937)</bibRefCitation>
evidently knew 
<bibRefCitation author="Salem, HH" journalOrPublisher="Faculty of Medicine" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" pagination="1 - 61" refId="B33" refString="Salem, HH, 1935. The Egyptian species of the genus Sarcophaga. Publications of the Egypt University. Faculty of Medicine 5: 1 - 61" title="The Egyptian species of the genus Sarcophaga. Publications of the Egypt University." volume="5" year="1935">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Salem’s">Salem's</normalizedToken>
(1935)
</bibRefCitation>
work on 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1824" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Sarcophaga" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sarcophaga" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">Sarcophaga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(s.l.) from Egypt, but he did not study any material identified as 
<taxonomicName family="Sarcophagidae" genus="S." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="S. aegyptica" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" rank="species" species="aegyptica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">S. aegyptica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and therefore quoted 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Salem’s">Salem's</normalizedToken>
description. Furthermore, the diagnostic differences in the shape of the juxtal arms and harpes outlined in the key by 
<bibRefCitation author="Rohdendorf, BB" journalOrPublisher="Izdatelstvo Akademii Nauk SSSR, Moskva-Leningrad" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" refId="B30" refString="Rohdendorf, BB, 1937. Fam. Sarcophagidae (part 1), Fauna SSSR, New Series, No. 12. Izdatelstvo Akademii Nauk SSSR, Moskva-Leningrad" title="Fam. Sarcophagidae (part 1), Fauna SSSR, New Series, No. 12." year="1937">Rohdendorf (1937</bibRefCitation>
: 440) were assessed based on 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Salem’s">Salem's</normalizedToken>
illustrations. 
<bibRefCitation author="Gregor, F" journalOrPublisher="Acta Societatis Entomologicae Cechoslovenicae" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" pagination="158 - 177" refId="B12" refString="Gregor, F, Povolny, D, 1960. Beitrag zur Kenntnis der synanthroper Fliegen Ungarns. Acta Societatis Entomologicae Cechoslovenicae 57 (2): 158 - 177" title="Beitrag zur Kenntnis der synanthroper Fliegen Ungarns." volume="57" year="1960">
Gregor and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Povolný">Povolny</normalizedToken>
(1960)
</bibRefCitation>
synonymized the two nominal species, which was accepted by 
<bibRefCitation author="Rohdendorf, BB" journalOrPublisher=") Keys to the Insects of the European Part of the USSR" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" pagination="624 - 670" refId="B32" refString="Rohdendorf, BB, 1970. [Fam. Sarcophagidae - sarcophagids.] In: Bei-Bienko GYa (Ed.) Keys to the Insects of the European Part of the USSR 5 (2): 624 - 670" title="[Fam. Sarcophagidae - sarcophagids.] In: Bei-Bienko GYa (Ed." volume="5" year="1970">Rohdendorf (1970)</bibRefCitation>
, and these taxa have since been considered either as separate species, e.g., by 
<bibRefCitation author="Lehrer, AZ" journalOrPublisher="Serie de Biologie Animale" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" pagination="11 - 17" refId="B14" refString="Lehrer, AZ, 1995. Distinction taxonomique entre les especes palearctiques Liosarcophaga aegyptica (Salem) et Liosarcophaga parkeri (Rohdendorf) et description de deux especes nouvelles afrotropicales (Diptera, Sarcophagidae). Revue Roumaine de Biologie. Serie de Biologie Animale 40 (1): 11 - 17" title="Distinction taxonomique entre les especes palearctiques Liosarcophaga aegyptica (Salem) et Liosarcophaga parkeri (Rohdendorf) et description de deux especes nouvelles afrotropicales (Diptera, Sarcophagidae). Revue Roumaine de Biologie." volume="40" year="1995">Lehrer (1995)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Pape, T" journalOrPublisher="International" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" pagination="1 - 558" refId="B22" refString="Pape, T, 1996. Catalogue of the Sarcophagidae of the world (Insecta: Diptera). Memoirs on Entomology. International 8: 1 - 558" title="Catalogue of the Sarcophagidae of the world (Insecta: Diptera). Memoirs on Entomology." volume="8" year="1996">Pape (1996)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.4001/003.026.0507" author="El-Ahmady, A" journalOrPublisher="African Entomology" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" pagination="507 - 521" refId="B5" refString="El-Ahmady, A, Taha, M, Soliman, AM, El-Hawagry, M, 2018. A new species and new records of the genus Sarcophaga from Egypt, with a key to the known Egyptian species (Diptera: Sarcophagidae). African Entomology 26 (2): 507 - 521, DOI: https://doi.org/10.4001/003.026.0507" title="A new species and new records of the genus Sarcophaga from Egypt, with a key to the known Egyptian species (Diptera: Sarcophagidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.4001/003.026.0507" volume="26" year="2018">El-Ahmady et al. (2018)</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<bibRefCitation author="Verves, YuG" journalOrPublisher="Priamus" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" pagination="1 - 282" refId="B37" refString="Verves, YuG, Khrokalo, LA, 2020. Review of the taxa of Calliphoridae and Sarcophagidae (Diptera) studied by the late Prof. Andy Z. Lehrer. Priamus 44: 1 - 282" title="Review of the taxa of Calliphoridae and Sarcophagidae (Diptera) studied by the late Prof. Andy Z. Lehrer." volume="44" year="2020">Verves and Khrokalo (2020)</bibRefCitation>
, or as synonyms, e.g., by 
<bibRefCitation author="Xue, Wq" journalOrPublisher="Liaoning Science and Technology Press, Shenyang" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" refId="B44" refString="Xue, Wq, Chao, Cm, 1998. Flies of China. Liaoning Science and Technology Press, Shenyang" title="Flies of China." year="1998">Xue and Chao (1998)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Nandi, BC" journalOrPublisher="Acta medica Universitatis Kagoshima" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" refId="B20" refString="Nandi, BC, 2002. DipteraSarcophagidae. Zoological Survey of India 10: [i-xxiv,] 1-608." title="DipteraSarcophagidae. Zoological Survey of India 10: [i-xxiv,] 1 - 608." year="2002">Nandi (2002)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11118/actaun200452040091" author="Povolny, D" journalOrPublisher="Acta Universitatis Agriculturae et Silviculturae Mendelianae Brunensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" pagination="91 - 101" refId="B27" refString="Povolny, D, Hula, V, 2004. On an invasion of the flesh-fly Liosarcophaga aegyptica (Salem, 1935) into Central Europe with the discovery of Helicophagella verstraeteni (Lehrer, 1975) in East Slovakia (Diptera, Sarcophagidae). Acta Universitatis Agriculturae et Silviculturae Mendelianae Brunensis 52 (4): 91 - 101, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11118/actaun200452040091" title="On an invasion of the flesh-fly Liosarcophaga aegyptica (Salem, 1935) into Central Europe with the discovery of Helicophagella verstraeteni (Lehrer, 1975) in East Slovakia (Diptera, Sarcophagidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.11118/actaun200452040091" volume="52" year="2004">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Povolný">Povolny</normalizedToken>
and Hula (2004)
</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<bibRefCitation author="Richet, R" journalOrPublisher="Pensoft Publishers, Sofia" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" refId="B28" refString="Richet, R, Blackith, RM, Pape, T, 2011. Sarcophaga of France (Diptera: Sarcophagidae). Pensoft Publishers, Sofia" title="Sarcophaga of France (Diptera: Sarcophagidae)." year="2011">Richet et al. (2011)</bibRefCitation>
. The recent conspectus of Egyptian species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1824" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Sarcophaga" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sarcophaga" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">Sarcophaga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(s.l.) by 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.4001/003.026.0507" author="El-Ahmady, A" journalOrPublisher="African Entomology" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" pagination="507 - 521" refId="B5" refString="El-Ahmady, A, Taha, M, Soliman, AM, El-Hawagry, M, 2018. A new species and new records of the genus Sarcophaga from Egypt, with a key to the known Egyptian species (Diptera: Sarcophagidae). African Entomology 26 (2): 507 - 521, DOI: https://doi.org/10.4001/003.026.0507" title="A new species and new records of the genus Sarcophaga from Egypt, with a key to the known Egyptian species (Diptera: Sarcophagidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.4001/003.026.0507" volume="26" year="2018">El-Ahmady et al. (2018)</bibRefCitation>
separated 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Salem" authorityYear="1935" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Sarcophaga" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sarcophaga aegyptica" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aegyptica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">Sarcophaga aegyptica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Aldrich" authorityYear="1916" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Sarcophaga" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sarcophaga parkeri" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parkeri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">Sarcophaga parkeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by vesica with two short processes apically and narrow harpes (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Salem" authorityYear="1935" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Sarcophaga" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sarcophaga aegyptica" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aegyptica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">Sarcophaga aegyptica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) versus vesica with three short processes apically and broad harpes (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Aldrich" authorityYear="1916" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Sarcophaga" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sarcophaga parkeri" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parkeri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">Sarcophaga parkeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The material at our disposal was not sufficient for a thorough assessment of the relevant morphological characters, but we have the impression that both the vesica and the harpes are variable structures, which furthermore present themselves very differently depending on the type of preparation and condition of the specimen. We have therefore chosen a conservative approach and consider the two nominal taxa as synonyms.
</paragraph>
